276
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:05,130
It can increase the risk of infection and delayed healing.

277
00:14:05,130 --> 00:14:07,810
So... it's hard to say.

278
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:09,680
I can only tell you

279
00:14:09,990 --> 00:14:11,160
it's possible to restore the basic function

280
00:14:11,160 --> 00:14:13,150
in five months.

281
00:14:32,760 --> 00:14:33,660
Doctor, thank you.

282
00:14:33,660 --> 00:14:34,320
No big deal.

283
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:40,300
What did the doctor tell you just now?

284
00:14:42,210 --> 00:14:43,790
He said I'm recovering well.

285
00:14:43,790 --> 00:14:44,760
Don't worry.

286
00:14:58,960 --> 00:15:00,280
I'm a little tired today.

287
00:15:00,280 --> 00:15:01,360
Go back first.

288
00:15:04,040 --> 00:15:05,030
Didn't you say...

289
00:15:05,030 --> 00:15:06,000
you're thirsty?

290
00:15:07,150 --> 00:15:07,950
Yes.

291
00:15:08,360 --> 00:15:09,160
Give it to me.

292
00:15:09,250 --> 00:15:10,850
I ran around this afternoon.

293
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:12,030
I'm exhausted.

294
00:15:12,390 --> 00:15:13,560
Go back first.

295
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:21,640
I'm leaving then.

296
00:16:14,160 --> 00:16:14,960
Mr. Xu.

297
00:16:15,830 --> 00:16:17,160
Have you seen Xue Yiran?

298
00:16:18,020 --> 00:16:19,170
Talk to him.

299
00:16:19,470 --> 00:16:21,000
Look at his X-ray film.

300
00:16:21,190 --> 00:16:22,880
The rupture is so serious.

301
00:16:23,010 --> 00:16:24,430
But he still won't have an operation.

302
00:16:24,430 --> 00:16:25,850
He still wants to take part in competitions.

303
00:16:25,850 --> 00:16:28,850
He even forced me to give him conservative treatment.

304
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:34,040
Mr. Xu,

305
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:35,480
I have a question.

306
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:38,350
If he has an operation,

307
00:16:38,690 --> 00:16:40,490
can he recover to his best level?

308
00:16:43,190 --> 00:16:44,120
It's hard to say.

309
00:16:44,660 --> 00:16:47,320
It depends on your psychological expectation.

310
00:16:47,650 --> 00:16:49,370
Maybe Olympic champions can

311
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:50,860
because they

312
00:16:50,980 --> 00:16:52,310
have top-notch doctors

313
00:16:52,510 --> 00:16:54,460
and nursing teams

314
00:16:54,630 --> 00:16:56,230
and they are very self-disciplined.

315
00:16:56,230 --> 00:16:57,290
But you should know

316
00:16:57,470 --> 00:16:59,070
once a rubber band breaks,

317
00:16:59,180 --> 00:17:01,030
it can't endure repeated stretching anymore.

318
00:17:01,030 --> 00:17:02,590
Even if it can be completely restored,

319
00:17:02,590 --> 00:17:05,520
it'll be more fragile than one that has never broken.

320
00:17:07,550 --> 00:17:09,150
Do you know fault tolerance?

321
00:17:09,530 --> 00:17:12,990
For someone who's at the same level as him but has higher fault tolerance,

322
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:14,560
no matter what that person does within reasonable limits,

323
00:17:14,560 --> 00:17:15,839
it won't matter.

324
00:17:16,050 --> 00:17:16,890
But for him,

325
00:17:17,180 --> 00:17:18,400
if anything goes wrong,

326
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:20,130
all the efforts will be in vain.

327
00:17:52,520 --> 00:17:55,740
♫I want to travel to the future to see if I'm okay♫

328
00:17:55,910 --> 00:17:58,570
♫Will I still cry at 3 a.m.?♫

329
00:17:58,750 --> 00:18:01,930
♫Don't just drink beer when you're depressed and sad♫

330
00:18:02,340 --> 00:18:04,320
♫It can't solve your problems in life♫

331
00:18:04,590 --> 00:18:07,470
♫This will make you fall apart, so please stop♫

332
00:18:07,740 --> 00:18:10,480
♫But I don't know when my dream can come true♫

333
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:13,230
♫I've had enough, but I still remember what you said♫

334
00:18:13,710 --> 00:18:15,350
♫You said don't be afraid♫

335
00:18:16,060 --> 00:18:20,940
♫Once promises are made, I never thought of leaving♫

336
00:18:21,860 --> 00:18:26,930
♫Despite numerous challenges♫

337
00:18:27,890 --> 00:18:32,150
♫The wish made in summer will eventually come true♫

338
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:37,230
♫My dream has never disappeared♫

339
00:19:00,750 --> 00:19:02,610
You're here drinking wine alone?

340
00:19:07,120 --> 00:19:08,520
How did you know I'm here?

341
00:19:10,020 --> 00:19:12,080
You just won't let me drink secretly.

342
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:15,690
You haven't recovered yet.

343
00:19:16,790 --> 00:19:19,590
I think the doctor has forbidden you to drink wine.

344
00:19:24,640 --> 00:19:25,560
I want to drink.

345
00:19:34,230 --> 00:19:35,830
Is the competition in August

346
00:19:37,480 --> 00:19:39,140
really that important to you?

347
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:49,920
Why did you refuse to have an operation?

348
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:54,260
I don't want to have an operation.

349
00:19:58,920 --> 00:19:59,910
Why?

350
00:20:03,270 --> 00:20:04,880
It's already ruptured.

351
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:06,430
Do you want to have an operation

352
00:20:06,430 --> 00:20:08,560
only when it's completely fractured?

353
00:20:08,690 --> 00:20:10,520
Besides, even if you have an operation now,

354
00:20:10,520 --> 00:20:11,920
it'll be very difficult to recover to your best level.

355
00:20:11,920 --> 00:20:12,850
Do you know that?

356
00:20:15,960 --> 00:20:17,400
Aren't you worried

357
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:19,200
about your sports career at all?

358
00:20:21,350 --> 00:20:22,080
You

359
00:20:25,350 --> 00:20:26,680
like running so much.

360
00:20:31,430 --> 00:20:32,240
Why?

361
00:20:33,910 --> 00:20:34,590
It's just

362
00:20:34,590 --> 00:20:37,650
the National College Students Athletics Tournament.

363
00:20:39,190 --> 00:20:40,230
If you recover,

364
00:20:41,060 --> 00:20:44,120
you'll have many opportunities to take part in competitions.

365
00:20:44,120 --> 00:20:46,780
Why do you have to take part in this competition?

366
00:20:48,360 --> 00:20:49,160
Because...

367
00:20:55,520 --> 00:20:57,250
I want to graduate with a smile.

368
00:20:59,840 --> 00:21:00,500
Because...

369
00:21:03,240 --> 00:21:05,670
I want to graduate without any guilt.

370
00:21:07,380 --> 00:21:08,780
I want to graduate calmly

371
00:21:10,210 --> 00:21:11,670
and with a smile on my face.

372
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:13,690
Because...

373
00:21:18,380 --> 00:21:19,780
this is my promise to him.

374
00:21:23,040 --> 00:21:24,370
It would be meaningless

375
00:21:27,130 --> 00:21:28,790
if it's another competition.

376
00:21:37,480 --> 00:21:38,230
Guys,

377
00:21:38,320 --> 00:21:39,720
our new jerseys are here.

378
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:44,040
Here.

379
00:21:44,850 --> 00:21:46,720
There's a name abbreviation on the back.

380
00:21:46,720 --> 00:21:47,550
It's cool, right?

381
00:21:47,550 --> 00:21:50,080
I specially asked someone to customize them.

382
00:21:50,160 --> 00:21:50,920
Ziji.

383
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:51,960
This is yours.

384
00:21:52,090 --> 00:21:54,080
Do you have a name abbreviation on it?

385
00:21:54,080 --> 00:21:54,680
Let me see.

386
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:00,690
My uniform has a name abbreviation too?

387
00:22:00,690 --> 00:22:01,370
Of course.

388
00:22:01,930 --> 00:22:03,330
Is the material the same?

389
00:22:03,560 --> 00:22:04,600
Of course.

390
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:06,060
Why would it be different?

391
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:08,460
What's the size of my uniform?

392
00:22:08,460 --> 00:22:09,500
M or L?

393
00:22:10,090 --> 00:22:10,740
Xue Yiran.

394
00:22:10,760 --> 00:22:12,020
Open it and take a look.

395
00:22:12,360 --> 00:22:13,760
This is your new uniform.

396
00:22:18,080 --> 00:22:19,680
It's different from theirs.

397
00:22:20,310 --> 00:22:21,110
Boring.

398
00:22:22,750 --> 00:22:23,920
I think

399
00:22:24,600 --> 00:22:25,810
it suits me well.

400
00:22:25,840 --> 00:22:26,680
It's beautiful.

401
00:22:26,680 --> 00:22:27,480
Of course.

402
00:22:28,760 --> 00:22:30,120
He's more capable than us.

403
00:22:30,120 --> 00:22:30,920
What's the big deal?

404
00:22:30,920 --> 00:22:31,780
Don't say that.

405
00:22:31,890 --> 00:22:32,770
We can't expect

406
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:34,550
everyone to have the same personality.

407
00:22:34,550 --> 00:22:36,000
Besides, he really is awesome.

408
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:37,310
It's normal that

409
00:22:37,310 --> 00:22:38,270
he looks down on us.

410
00:22:38,270 --> 00:22:40,150
Not us, just you, okay?

411
00:22:40,760 --> 00:22:42,000
Is Xue Yiran

412
00:22:42,030 --> 00:22:43,290
better than you or not?

413
00:22:44,560 --> 00:22:45,400
Yes.

414
00:22:45,420 --> 00:22:47,520
You have to admit that he is amazing.

415
00:22:47,630 --> 00:22:48,600
Go!

416
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:49,860
Xue Yiran, come on!

417
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:53,750
Come on, Xue Yiran!

418
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:55,970
Come on!

419
00:22:58,700 --> 00:22:59,730
Xue Yiran.

420
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:04,720
Xue Yiran.

421
00:23:05,320 --> 00:23:06,640
I bought braised pork ribs.

422
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:07,520
Do you want some?

423
00:23:07,520 --> 00:23:08,560
I don't like it.

424
00:23:08,580 --> 00:23:09,510
What do you like?

425
00:23:09,540 --> 00:23:10,600
I'll buy it for you.

426
00:23:14,690 --> 00:23:16,490
Why are you always so nice to him?

427
00:23:17,590 --> 00:23:19,670
I've been weak since I was a kid.

428
00:23:19,700 --> 00:23:21,560
So my parents asked me to practice running.

429
00:23:21,560 --> 00:23:23,240
Even though I trained really hard,

430
00:23:23,240 --> 00:23:24,990
I only achieved a result of about 11.5 seconds.

431
00:23:24,990 --> 00:23:26,070
So I envy

432
00:23:26,070 --> 00:23:27,840
athletes like Xue Yiran very much.

433
00:23:27,840 --> 00:23:28,750
He absolutely has the chance

434
00:23:28,750 --> 00:23:30,210
to stand on a bigger stage.

435
00:23:30,520 --> 00:23:31,360
I

436
00:23:31,380 --> 00:23:33,200
am willing to do my best to help him,

437
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:34,000
support him,

438
00:23:34,020 --> 00:23:35,540
and shine for him.

439
00:23:38,300 --> 00:23:40,230
You just won't listen to me, right?

440
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:41,990
Why won't you participate

441
00:23:41,990 --> 00:23:43,390
in the 4 x 100 m relay race?

442
00:23:43,640 --> 00:23:45,300
Because it will waste my physical strength

443
00:23:45,300 --> 00:23:47,270
and influence my performance in the 100 m race.

444
00:23:47,270 --> 00:23:49,680
You're not the only one who'll participate in the 100 m race.

445
00:23:49,680 --> 00:23:50,770
You think you are special?

446
00:23:50,770 --> 00:23:52,650
You don't care about the Track and Field Club at all.

447
00:23:52,650 --> 00:23:55,190
When you left for the provincial team's training and asked for a leave,

448
00:23:55,190 --> 00:23:56,890
did I make things difficult for you?

449
00:23:56,890 --> 00:23:58,590
Why is it so hard

450
00:23:58,730 --> 00:24:00,240
to make you contribute to the team?

451
00:24:00,240 --> 00:24:01,560
Actually, it doesn't matter

452
00:24:01,560 --> 00:24:03,400
whether I'm in the school team or not.

453
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:05,000
The principal asked me here.

454
00:24:05,530 --> 00:24:07,160
You're using the principal to put pressure on me, right?

455
00:24:07,160 --> 00:24:07,910
If you look down on us,

456
00:24:07,910 --> 00:24:08,840
don't come here.

457
00:24:09,900 --> 00:24:11,020
How arrogant!

458
00:24:12,300 --> 00:24:12,860
Fei Zhe,

459
00:24:12,880 --> 00:24:13,320
what's wrong?

460
00:24:13,320 --> 00:24:14,050
Are you okay?

461
00:24:14,920 --> 00:24:15,800
I'm fine.

462
00:24:15,830 --> 00:24:16,360
Sir,

463
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:17,550
you were so fierce just now.

464
00:24:17,550 --> 00:24:19,330
I nearly had a heart attack because of you.

465
00:24:19,330 --> 00:24:21,080
Stay at home if you're sick.

466
00:24:21,590 --> 00:24:22,560
You guys...

467
00:24:32,670 --> 00:24:33,800
What's on your mind?

468
00:24:35,680 --> 00:24:36,760
You've recovered?

469
00:24:37,280 --> 00:24:38,360
Don't worry about me.

470
00:24:38,360 --> 00:24:39,400
I pretended

471
00:24:39,520 --> 00:24:40,780
to have a heart attack.

472
00:24:42,220 --> 00:24:43,990
Considering the situation this afternoon,

473
00:24:43,990 --> 00:24:45,970
if I didn't pretend to be sick to interrupt you,

474
00:24:45,970 --> 00:24:47,630
you two would have fallen out.

475
00:24:48,910 --> 00:24:50,060
I don't care.

476
00:24:50,810 --> 00:24:51,960
Easy for you to say.

477
00:24:52,230 --> 00:24:53,360
The coach said those words this afternoon

478
00:24:53,360 --> 00:24:54,410
out of anger.

479
00:24:54,600 --> 00:24:55,790
Everyone can see

480
00:24:55,790 --> 00:24:57,230
how much importance he attaches to you.

481
00:24:57,230 --> 00:24:58,160
Besides, do you really want

482
00:24:58,160 --> 00:24:59,580
to withdraw from the Track and Field Club?

483
00:24:59,580 --> 00:25:02,040
If so, how will you explain to the principal?

484
00:25:02,800 --> 00:25:04,360
Our coach is straightforward.

485
00:25:04,360 --> 00:25:05,800
He doesn't have any evil intentions.

486
00:25:05,800 --> 00:25:07,990
He just wants you to contribute more to the team.

487
00:25:07,990 --> 00:25:09,400
After all, you are very capable.

488
00:25:09,400 --> 00:25:11,320
Arguing with him can't solve the problem.

489
00:25:11,320 --> 00:25:13,050
It will only make things worse.

490
00:25:23,750 --> 00:25:25,090
[Mom]

491
00:25:47,800 --> 00:25:48,600
Hello.

492
00:25:48,750 --> 00:25:49,560
Ran,

493
00:25:49,960 --> 00:25:50,620
why did you suddenly

494
00:25:50,620 --> 00:25:52,100
call me today?

495
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:53,260
What's the matter?

496
00:25:53,360 --> 00:25:54,160
Mom.

497
00:25:54,970 --> 00:25:55,860
Nothing.

498
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:57,640
I just want to ask you

499
00:25:57,640 --> 00:25:58,870
how you've been.

500
00:26:00,480 --> 00:26:01,400
Not bad.

501
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:02,570
Son, what about you?

502
00:26:03,810 --> 00:26:04,870
I've been fine too.

503
00:26:05,560 --> 00:26:06,720
I achieved better results.

504
00:26:06,720 --> 00:26:07,160
Mom,

505
00:26:07,160 --> 00:26:08,490
I want to eat pineapple.

506
00:26:09,680 --> 00:26:10,240
Son,

507
00:26:10,240 --> 00:26:11,270
I have to go.

508
00:26:11,270 --> 00:26:12,600
Tong is back.

509
00:26:15,630 --> 00:26:21,030
♫A fleeting beam of light♫

510
00:26:21,530 --> 00:26:27,540
♫The youth wants to catch up to the sun♫

511
00:26:27,650 --> 00:26:33,010
♫My dream makes me♫

512
00:26:33,030 --> 00:26:36,010
♫Willing to be crazy♫

513
00:26:35,270 --> 00:26:37,750
[Fei Zhe]

514
00:26:39,340 --> 00:26:45,050
♫Breaking through fear, racing against destiny♫

515
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:43,680
Hello.

516
00:26:44,600 --> 00:26:45,400
Xue Yiran,

517
00:26:45,170 --> 00:26:50,770
♫Not being nervous anymore, not being content with the status quo♫

518
00:26:45,560 --> 00:26:46,560
are you at school?

519
00:26:47,880 --> 00:26:50,080
Can you come to the Track and Field Club?

520
00:26:50,390 --> 00:26:51,870
Why should I go to the Track and Field Club?

521
00:26:51,560 --> 00:26:57,070
♫Never again♫

522
00:26:52,230 --> 00:26:53,030
Come here now.

523
00:26:53,120 --> 00:26:53,960
The coach wants to talk to you

524
00:26:53,960 --> 00:26:55,580
about the future training plan.

525
00:26:55,580 --> 00:26:56,320
Got it.

526
00:26:57,360 --> 00:26:59,860
♫Feel lost♫

527
00:27:01,180 --> 00:27:06,260
♫Once promises are made, I never thought of leaving♫

528
00:27:06,460 --> 00:27:11,480
♫Even facing the hardships of reality♫

529
00:27:08,980 --> 00:27:10,480
[Happy birthday]

530
00:27:12,880 --> 00:27:13,870
Surprise!

531
00:27:13,220 --> 00:27:17,840
♫The wish made in summer will come true♫

532
00:27:13,870 --> 00:27:17,390
-Happy birthday!
-Happy birthday!

533
00:27:18,060 --> 00:27:22,640
♫My dream has never disappeared♫

534
00:27:25,300 --> 00:27:30,940
♫Failure is better than boredom♫
